						<div class="postbody">The carry flag is set if the value in X is greather or equal than the value in memory (ungisned), and clear if the value in X is smaller than the value in memory.
<br />
<br />Think as if "memory" was substracted from X as if it was a SBC opcode (also it doesn't substract one more even if C was set prior to the compare), but the resuls is discared, only the flags are taken over</div>

					
